\f0\fs28 \cf2 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1 Today is the anniversary of the death of Sir William Rowan Hamilton (1805-1865) , Irish mathematician that gave important contributions to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Optics"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 optics}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 classical mechanics}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebra"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 algebra}}. \
Although Hamilton regarded himself as a pure mathematician, his work was of major importance to physics: his reformulation of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newtonian_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 Newtonian mechanics}}, now called {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamiltonian_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 Hamiltonian mechanics}}, is a standard topic in graduate courses. This work has proven central to the modern study of classical field theories such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electromagnetism"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 electromagnetism}}, and to the development of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 quantum mechanics}}. In pure mathematics, he is best known as the inventor of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quaternion"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 quaternions}}.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f1 Si celebra oggi l anniversario della nascita di Sir William Rowan Hamilton, matematico irlandese che ha dato fondamentali contributi sia alla matematica pura che alla matematica. La sua riformulazione della meccanica Newtoniana, oggi nota come meccanica Hamiltoniana, \'e9 stato un passo fondamentale per lo sviluppo delle teoria dell\'92elettromagnetismo e della meccanica quantistica. Nella matematica pura rimane noto per l\'92invenzione dei quaternioni.\
In suo onore sono state nominate una funzione in matematica, un operatore in meccanica quantistica e addirittura un tipo di grafo.  Il teorema di Cayley-Hamilton, l'equazione di Hamilton-Jacobi e il principio di Hamilton sono altri esempi che portano il suo nome.\
